{"title_page": "Silent protest", "text_new": "'''Silent protest''' is an organized effort where the participants stay quiet to demonstrate disapproval. It is used as a form of [[civil disobedience]] and [[nonviolent resistance]].<ref name=BBC>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/onthisday/hi/dates/stories/october/17/newsid_3535000/3535348.stm 1968: Black athletes make silent protest]</ref>\n\n==Examples==\n* On July 28, 1917, a [[Silent Parade]] took place in [[New York City]] to protest [[lynching]].\n* [[1968 Olympics Black Power salute]]\n*[[1968 Summer Olympics]] \u2013 Czech gymnast [[V\u011bra \u010c\u00e1slavsk\u00e1]] looked away when the Soviet anthem was playing<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.radio.cz/en/section/curraffrs/vera-caslavskas-silent-protest-at-1968-olympics-recalled|title=V\u011bra \u010c\u00e1slavsk\u00e1\u2019s silent protest at 1968 Olympics recalled {{!}} Radio Prague|website=Radio Praha|language=en|access-date=2019-08-30}}</ref>\n* [[NOH8 Campaign]]\n* [[2011 Belarusian protests]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n\n[[Category:Community organizing]]\n[[Category:Nonviolence]]\n[[Category:Protest tactics]]\n\n\n{{activism-stub}}\n", "text_old": "'''Silent protest''' is an organized effort where the participants stay quiet to demonstrate disapproval. It is used as a form of [[civil disobedience]] and [[nonviolent resistance]].<ref name=BBC>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/onthisday/hi/dates/stories/october/17/newsid_3535000/3535348.stm 1968: Black athletes make silent protest]</ref>\n\n==Examples==\n* On July 28, 1917, a [[Silent Parade]] took place in [[New York City]] to protest [[lynching]].\n* [[1968 Olympics Black Power salute]]\n*[[1968 Summer Olympics]] \u2013 czech gymnast [[V\u011bra \u010c\u00e1slavsk\u00e1]] looked away when the Soviet anthem was playing<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.radio.cz/en/section/curraffrs/vera-caslavskas-silent-protest-at-1968-olympics-recalled|title=V\u011bra \u010c\u00e1slavsk\u00e1\u2019s silent protest at 1968 Olympics recalled