gory:Immigration]]\n[[Category:Majority\u2013minority relations]]\n", "text_old": "'''Immigrant Food''' is a \u201ccause-casual\u201d restaurant in Washington D.C.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/lifestyle/food/a-new-dc-restaurant-will-promote-immigrant-causes-right-in-trumps-front-yard/2019/11/11/dc31d598-0001-11ea-8bab-0fc209e065a8_story.html|title=A new D.C. restaurant will promote immigrant causes right in Trump\u2019s front yard|last=Carman|first=Tim|date=|website=The Washington Post|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonian.com/2019/10/03/advocacy-fast-casual-restaurant-immigrant-food-is-opening-by-the-white-house/|title=An Advocacy Restaurant Called \"Immigrant Food\" Is Opening by the White House|date=2019-10-03|website=Washingtonian|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref> Located near the [[White House]], the restaurant combines its food offerings with pro-immigrant activism.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/2019/12/01/784005867/immigrant-food-restaurant-trumps-new-neighbor|title='Immigrant Food' Restaurant, Trump's New Neighbor|website=NPR.org|language=en|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/briannegarrett/2019/11/14/a-restaurant-serving-immigrant-causes-opens-steps-away-from-the-white-house/|title=A Restaurant Serving Immigrant Causes Opens Steps Away From The White House|last=Garrett|first=Brianne|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n\nImmigrant Food serves fusion food from China, El Salvador, Ethiopia, and other countries.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dc.eater.com/2019/11/11/20955247/immigrant-food-restaurant-opening-white-house-downtown-dc-fusion-bowls-mylks|title=A New Fast-Casual Place Called Immigrant Food Preaches \u2018Gastroadvocacy\u2019 in Trump\u2019s Backyard|last=Adkins|first=Lenore|date=2019-11-11|website=Eater DC|language=en|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref> Its menu was prepared by cel